Document: OpenXRAnalogThresholdModifier  
Path: godot/classes/class_openxranalogthresholdmodifier.rst  
Summary: Properties and their default values for the OpenXRAnalogThresholdModifier class.  

- off_haptic (OpenXRHapticBase): The haptic effect to apply when the analog threshold is not met. Default: None.  
- off_threshold (float): The analog threshold value below which the off_haptic effect is triggered. Default: 0.4.  
- on_haptic (OpenXRHapticBase): The haptic effect to apply when the analog threshold is met. Default: None.  
- on_threshold (float): The analog threshold value above which the on_haptic effect is triggered. Default: 0.6.
---CHUNK---
Document: OpenXRAnalogThresholdModifier  
Path: godot/classes/class_openxranalogthresholdmodifier.rst  
Summary: Properties for configuring haptic feedback and threshold behavior in OpenXRAnalogThresholdModifier.  

off_haptic (OpenXRHapticBase): Haptic pulse to emit when the user releases the input. Set via set_off_haptic(OpenXRHapticBase), retrieved via get_off_haptic().  
off_threshold (float, default: 0.4): When input value falls below this, output becomes false. Set via set_off_threshold(float), retrieved via get_off_threshold().  
on_haptic (OpenXRHapticBase): Haptic pulse to emit when the user presses the input. Set via set_on_haptic(OpenXRHapticBase), retrieved via get_on_haptic().  
on_threshold (float, default: 0.6): When input value is equal or larger than this, output becomes true. It stays true until it falls under the off_threshold value. Set via set_on_threshold(float), retrieved via get_on_threshold().